<p itemprop="description">The head of command and control centre management provides strategic leadership for all operational coordination activities across the organisation. They establish enterprise-wide operational frameworks and ensure organisational resilience and operational excellence.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide strategic leadership for operational coordination across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish enterprise-wide operational frameworks and governance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead organisational resilience and business continuity initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive digital transformation of operational capabilities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent operational interests in executive and board-level discussions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure alignment with regulatory and compliance requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop strategic partnerships with external operational service providers</li>
    </ul>
</section>

